# Rule 03 — Vue 3 + TypeScript Architecture

> Governs component **logic & structure** ONLY. All visual/CSS output MUST obey `00-unocss-guardrails.mdc`.

---

## 1. Script Setup Macro Ordering (REQUIRED)

Fixed declaration order within `<script setup lang="ts">`:

```
1. defineOptions()        — component name, inheritAttrs
2. defineProps<T>()       — input contract
3. defineEmits<T>()       — output contract
4. defineModel<T>()       — v-model bindings (if used)
5. defineSlots<T>()       — slot shape contract
6. --- business logic --- — ref, reactive, computed, watch, onMounted, functions...
7. defineExpose()         — imperative API (LAST, sparingly)
```

**Rules:**
- FORBIDDEN: `defineExpose` before business logic — it is always the LAST declaration
- FORBIDDEN: Business logic (ref, computed, watch) interleaved between macro declarations
- `defineOptions` MUST set `name` matching the PascalCase component filename

```vue
<!-- CORRECT -->
<script setup lang="ts">
defineOptions({ name: 'UserProfile' })

const props = defineProps<UserProfileProps>()
const emit = defineEmits<{ update: [user: User] }>()

// --- business logic starts here ---
const fullName = computed(() => `${props.firstName} ${props.lastName}`)
</script>
```

