## 8. Performance-Aware Reactivity

| Tool | When to Use |
|------|-------------|
| `v-once` | Truly static content that will never change (static headers, icon sets) |
| `v-memo` | List items with expensive rendering when key dependencies are known |
| `shallowRef` | Large external objects (ECharts instances, editor instances, map objects) |
| `markRaw` | Objects that must NEVER become reactive (third-party class instances, Web Workers) |

- **FORBIDDEN**: Deep watchers on large objects without explicit `{ deep: false }` override or a specific getter
- **REQUIRED**: Prefer `computed()` over methods for any value displayed in templates — caching prevents redundant recalculation

```ts
// CORRECT — shallowRef for chart instance (no need to proxy internals)
const chartInstance = shallowRef<ECharts | null>(null)

// CORRECT — markRaw for class instance
const editor = markRaw(new ExternalEditor(config))

// CORRECT — v-memo for list with known dependencies
// <div v-for="item in list" :key="item.id" v-memo="[item.id, item.updated]">
```

